{
  "texts": [
    "In the context of fossil image analysis, ViTs can significantly improve feature extraction and classification accuracy (Naseer et al. 2021; Bai et al. 2021).",
    "By leveraging pre-trained Vision Transformers, researchers can achieve enhanced performance in analyzing largescale fossil image datasets, effectively identifying and classifying fossils from extensive collections.",
    "This capability is particularly beneficial for tasks involving detailed and complex fossil features, providing a more precise and comprehensive analysis of fossil specimens.",
    "Hybrid models combine multiple algorithms or neural network architectures to leverage their respective strengths and mitigate their weaknesses (Fringer et al. 2006).",
    "As computa- tional power and DL have advanced, these hybrids have evolved from simple algorithmic combinations to complex neural network integrations (Engell et al. 2003; Marblestone et al. 2016; Zhang et al. 2020; Remadna et al. 2021; Li et al. 2023)."
  ]
}